## Whom to report a malicious IP to?

| Situation | Who you report to |
|---|---|
| Suspicious alert, unsure | Senior Analyst (L2) — Will Griffin in the room |
| Confirmed malicious, single device | Senior Analyst → they may loop in IR |
| Confirmed malicious, multiple devices or active breach | Senior Analyst escalates to Incident Responder (Daniel) |
| Major company-wide incident | Incident Responder + SOC Manager (Emily) involved |

**Rule of thumb:** When in doubt, escalate. In a SOC, under-escalating is worse
than over-escalating. You never want to sit on a confirmed threat.

